# MIGRATION STRATEGY: .NET / ASP.NET WEBFORMS

When encountering ASP.NET WebForms (`<asp:Content>`, `runat="server"`):

### 1. ViewState & PostBack
- **Concept:** WebForms relies on hidden `__VIEWSTATE` and full page PostBacks.
- **Rule:** Modern apps are Single Page. Ignore ViewState.
- **Action:** Convert `Page_Load` logic (checking `!IsPostBack`) to `useEffect` (initial load).
- **Action:** Convert Button `OnClick` (Server Event) to Client API calls.

### 2. Control Mapping
- `<asp:TextBox ID="txtEmail">` -> `<Input value={email} onChange={...} />`
- `<asp:Label>` -> `<span>` or `<Text>` component.
- `<asp:Repeater>` / `<asp:GridView>` -> `{items.map(item => <Row key={item.id} />)}`

### 3. Server Tags
- Remove `<%@ Page ... %>` directives.
- Remove `<form runat="server">` (React handles form submission via JS, not form posts).
